   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The inverter converts the DC input to an output AC. The inverter
is constantly synchronizing the voltage and frequency of the output
within tolerance of the bypass mains. This allows for an automatic
uninterrupted switch over to the bypass static switch.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">An output isolation transformer at the inverter output provides
galvanic separation and wide design range for the output voltages.</p>
